content:
We’ve expanded the functionality for Selective Sandbox Access! We now support providing access to a sandbox through a public group if your production org has 60 or more public groups. 

This change applies to sandboxes of Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Database.com editions.

All users in the production org with the Manage Dev Sandboxes (Developer or Developer Pro only) or Manage Sandboxes user permission can access the sandbox through a public group.

Selective Sandbox Access helps you limit access to a sandbox to only required users when refreshing or creating a sandbox. The email addresses for the users included in the group remain in their original format and don’t need to be modified. Users who aren’t part of the public group have to be unfrozen in the sandbox in order to access it.

If the production org has 60 or more public groups, enter a public group name for Sandbox Access when creating or refreshing a sandbox.
title: Selective Sandbox Access for Production Orgs
